  "prompt": "Which guitar should I buy in range of 7 to 8k?",
  "response": "When considering a guitar in the price range of 7,000 to 8,000 INR, you have several good options from reputable brands. Here are a few recommendations across different styles:\n\n### Acoustic Guitars\n\n1. **Yamaha F310**:\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b97,500\n   - **Features**: Spruce top, nato/okume back and sides, rosewood fingerboard, and a natural finish. It's known for its balanced tone and playability, making it great for beginners and intermediate players.\n\n2. **Kadence Frontier Series**:\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b97,500\n   - **Features**: Spruce top, mahogany back and sides, rosewood fingerboard, and a dreadnought body shape. It offers good sound quality and build for the price range.\n\n### Electric Guitars\n\n1. **Fender Squier Bullet Strat**:\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b97,500\n   - **Features**: Three single-coil pickups, a maple neck, and a tremolo bridge. It's a versatile guitar that can handle various genres and is great for beginners.\n\n2. **Ibanez GIO Series**:\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b97,500 - \u20b98,000\n   - **Features**: Typically equipped with humbucker pickups, a solid body, and a fast-playing neck. Good for rock and metal players looking for a budget-friendly option.\n\n### Considerations\n\n- **Skill Level**: If you're a beginner, the Yamaha F310 or Kadence Frontier might be more suitable due to their ease of play and forgiving nature.\n- **Genre**: Electric guitars like the Fender Squier or Ibanez GIO are better for rock, metal, and similar genres, while acoustic guitars are more versatile for folk, pop, and beginners.\n- **Build Quality**: Within this price range, you're looking at entry-level instruments. Pay attention to the feel of the neck, the action (string height), and the overall build quality when trying them out.\n\n### Where to Buy\n\n- **Online**: Amazon, Flipkart, and Bajaao are good places to start.\n- **In-Store**: Visit local music stores where you can try out the guitars before buying. This can be especially helpful if you're new to playing.\n\nRemember, the best guitar for you will depend on your personal preferences in terms of sound, feel, and style. If possible, try before you buy to ensure you're getting the best fit for your needs.",
